This paper proposes a novel technique for tackling the challenge of large vocabulary in recurrent neural networks (RNNs) for natural language processing tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also focuses on reducing the model size and speeding up the training process, which suggests that it could also belong to categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper evaluates its proposed algorithm using language modeling tasks, which could also place it in the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) category.
